  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;Unacceptable MIU delays&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Firstly I must say that I am a major supporter of the NHS system.However, I needed to attend the MIU following  a fall. I waited 30 mins before triage, 60min longer for practitioner,  further 45 min before X ray ... All this time the department was virtually empty, with patients attending other clinics only. My husband and I sat while a constant stream of staff came and went during this time, carrying food and drinks, obviously taking breaks.The quality of care was good, but the organisation was abysmal. Fortunately I was not in great pain at the beginning, but by the end I was in a lot of discomfort.. My husband and I are both business people and if we were to treat our customers as such we would soon be out of business.  Come on MIU - you should be better than this!&lt;/CommentText&gt;
